data.database_description: The database is designed to manage various aspects of a drama-related business, including clients, performers, workshop groups, stores, bookings, orders, services, and financial transactions like invoices. It tracks relationships between entities such as addresses, payment methods, and service types, ensuring comprehensive management of customer interactions, product sales, and performance scheduling within the organization.

columns.columnDescription: Unique code for each payment method.
Description or name of the payment method.
